{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":43635,"name":"MtrnXf","username":"MtrnXf","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/mtrnxf/{size}/3586_2.png","created_at":"2021-10-29T12:10:49.865Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello there. Ich have a model of a window of a building which geometry center is not at the middle of the object but at the left-bottom. Additionally the model is too huge according to it‚Äôs world (grid). So when rotating the model it‚Äôs not turning around it‚Äôs center but around point left-bottom like an egg. I tried to modify the model with ‚ÄúSetGeometryCenter(0,‚Ä¶)‚Äù method at runtime before adding it to the root node, but nothing changes.\u003cbr\u003e\nCan you help me with some code to modify the model so that it rotates around its center? Huge thanks\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://filehorst.de/d/eEHngial\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eLink to Window.mdl\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-10-29T12:17:03.212Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":10.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":7024,"topic_slug":"set-model-rotation-point-to-center","display_username":"MtrnXf","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://filehorst.de/d/eEHngial","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Window.mdl beim Filehorst - filehorst.de","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":43636,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2021-10-29T12:38:39.722Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe easiest way to fix transforms is on the level of Scene.\u003cbr\u003e\nE.g. if your model has wrong center, you:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAdd root node where the center of your model \u003cem\u003eshould\u003c/em\u003e be.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAdd child node used for offset.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAdd your model to child node.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMove child node used for offset so the center of the model is where you want it to be.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRotate root node.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-10-29T12:39:32.128Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":15.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":7024,"topic_slug":"set-model-rotation-point-to-center","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":43640,"name":"MtrnXf","username":"MtrnXf","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/mtrnxf/{size}/3586_2.png","created_at":"2021-10-29T21:43:02.898Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIt works, thank you \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/grinning.png?v=10\" title=\":grinning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":grinning:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e//Root node for rotation\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nNode rootNode = Scene.CreateChild(‚ÄúRootNode‚Äù);\u003cbr\u003e\nrootNode.Position = new Vector3(x: 0, y: 0, z: 0);\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e//Child node with negative offset to emulate new center of the model\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nNode childNode = rootNode.CreateChild(‚ÄúChildNode‚Äù);\u003cbr\u003e\nchildNode.Position = \u003cstrong\u003enew Vector3(x: -10, y: 0, z: 0);\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e//Model at child node\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nStaticModel model = childNode.CreateComponent();\u003cbr\u003e\nmodel.Model = ResourceCache.GetModel(‚ÄúWindow.mdl‚Äù);\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut at childNode.Position I have entered a fixed offset for x of -10 that works for my ‚ÄúWindow.mdl‚Äù. But how can I calculate the offset according to the size of the model?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRegards\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-10-29T21:43:02.898Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":10.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":7024,"topic_slug":"set-model-rotation-point-to-center","display_username":"MtrnXf","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":43641,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2021-10-29T22:05:06.702Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"MtrnXf\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"7024\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/mtrnxf/40/3586_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e MtrnXf:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut how can I calculate the offset according to the size of the model?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWell, you have access to BoundingBox of the Model.\u003cbr\u003e\nYou can deduce from there.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-10-29T22:05:06.702Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":25,"readers_count":24,"score":10.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7024,"topic_slug":"set-model-rotation-point-to-center","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":43667,"name":"MtrnXf","username":"MtrnXf","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/mtrnxf/{size}/3586_2.png","created_at":"2021-11-02T13:44:00.769Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIt‚Äôs working. Here is the code to center the model by moving the child node half the model size to the left:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003echildNode.Position = new Vector3(-1f * model.BoundingBox.HalfSize.X, 0, 0);\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe thing is, I have a model of a window in ‚Äúx3d‚Äù format which is used in the webbrowser. It has a texture (.jpg file), you can look through the glas of the window (half transparent) and the window has an open animation. I used AssetImporter_Win64.exe to convert the ‚Äúx3d‚Äù to a ‚Äúmdl‚Äù  (above file). The conversion is working, but after that the ‚Äúmdl‚Äù has no transparency of the glas anymore (you can‚Äôt look through the glas) and the texture is corrupt. The texture is not applied to the whole frame of the window anymore, only some parts. Do you have an hints on that?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e(Would be nice if Urho could import .x3d or .gltf format, but I did not find any information on that.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThank you. Regards\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-11-02T14:33:11.819Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":4.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7024,"topic_slug":"set-model-rotation-point-to-center","display_username":"MtrnXf","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":43687,"name":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2021-11-03T11:37:48.785Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u00